claim.t.sol
├── given Sablier NFT is staked
│   ├── when the caller is not same as the staker of the sablier NFT
│   │   └── it should revert
│   └── when the caller is same as the staker of the sablier NFT
│       ├── when the claim amount is zero
│       │   └── it should revert
│       └── when the claim amount is not zero
│           ├── given the balance of staking contracts is less than the claim amount
│           │   └── it should revert
│           └── given the balance of staking contracts is not less than the claim amount
│               ├── it should emit {ClaimAmountUpdated} event
│               ├── it should set staking rewards to zero
│               └── it should emit {Transfer} event
└── given Sablier NFT has been unstaked
    ├── when the caller is not same as the current recipient of the sablier NFT
    │   └── it should revert
    └── when the caller is same as the current recipient of the sablier NFT
        ├── when the claim amount is zero
        │   └── it should revert
        └── when the claim amount is not zero
            ├── it should set staking rewards to zero
            └── it should emit {Transfer} event
